summary: I think the Queen – I’m not sure I was ever a monarchist – is an incredibly impressive human being. And I’m slightly obsessed...
caption:
I think the Queen – I’m not sure I was ever a monarchist – is an incredibly impressive human being. And I’m slightly obsessed with her!

The voice department [on ‘The Crown’] are amazing and they’re there all the time. Even the word “television”, it’s a way of saying it, partly historical – she sort of has her own accent. The pitch has changed a bit through the years, as with all of us. “Television” it’s a [soft] ‘ieh’ sound [as in the word ‘if’] I enjoy all of those. That’s quite fun, going through all the sounds.

She in particular made a vow as a very young woman to serve her country. Which is an extraordinary thing to do. And she genuinely has stuck to it. I think that’s amazing!

– Olivia Colman on her new role as Queen Elizabeth II in ‘The Crown’ | 27 Jan 2019

David Tennant Does a Podcast With … Olivia Colman & her dog, Alfred Lord Waggyson

Image: Financial Times

body:
just listened to david tennant’s podcast with olivia colman and i came out with 3 things:

  1. olivia colman is utterly delightful and i can listen to her all day
  2. having tennant say he saw a therapist was a nice touch and i kinda wished he would talk about it more
  3. it was sooooo mellow … i could take a nap listening to this and i don’t know if that’s good or not yet lol
